<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="622" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways,
                                Inc./169: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bading</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-08T10:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            8, 1928—10 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>30. Pan American Airways, Incorporated, informs Department Mr. Harold
                                E. Harris, General Manager Peruvian Airways Corporation will assist
                                Mr. Otto Berg von Linde, representative of W. E. Grace and Company,
                                to apply for operating concession in Ecuador similar to concession
                                recently granted to Scadta.</p>
                            <p>Please render all possible and proper assistance. Department is much
                                interested in the development by American interests of commercial
                                aviation service between the United States and Latin America.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>